.TH FACIAL_TEST 1 "2025-01" "pam_facial_auth" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
facial_test \- test facial recognition for a given user

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B facial_test
\-u USER
[\-d DEVICE] [\-g] [\-v]
[\-m FILE] [\-c FILE]

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B facial_test
utility loads the trained XML facial model for the specified user and attempts
to authenticate using the webcam.

This is the standalone test tool and does not interact with PAM.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-u, --user USER
User whose model will be tested. Required.

.TP
.B \-d, --device DEVICE
Webcam device (default:
/dev/video0).

.TP
.B \-m, --model FILE
Model file path
(default:
/etc/pam_facial_auth/models/USER.xml).

.TP
.B \-g, --nogui
Disable GUI preview windows.

.TP
.B \-v, --verbose
Enable verbose logging.

.TP
.B \-c, --config FILE
Load settings from a configuration file
(default:
/etc/security/pam_facial.conf).

.TP
.B --help
Show help and exit.

.SH FILES
.TP
.B /etc/pam_facial_auth/models/USER.xml
Model file.
.TP
.B /etc/security/pam_facial.conf
Configuration file.

